1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the information-theoretic limits of energy-harvesting channels. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with the EH process and its characterization. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the achievable rates for channels under EH constraints. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the transmission of information over channels. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the lower bounds on achievable rates, which could have implications for secure communication.
